MyBroadband has launched its first Underground conference of 2018, which will take place at The Venue in Melrose Arch on 21 February 2018. This exclusive technical conference will focus on mobile networks and mobile networking technologies, and is presented in partnership with SqwidNet. Speakers at the MyBroadband Underground mobile networks and mobile networking technologies event include: The conference is aimed at IT executives and IT professionals who want to learn more about the latest developments in the mobile space. To register for, or learn more about, the MyBroadband Underground mobile networking conference, visit the conference website below. MyBroadband readers can also buy a ticket at a discounted price using the voucher code below. Please note that only 170 tickets are available for the event, and these seats will be allocated on a first-come-first-served basis. To see what delegates can look forward to, take a look at the inaugural MyBroadband Underground Conference in 2017.